title: Speaker Ryan calls failed health care vote frustrating
description:
(3 Aug 2017) US  House Speaker Paul Ryan faced questions from Republican voters in Wisconsin who say they are frustrated with a lack of action in Congress.
Ryan held a town hall meeting on Wednesday for employees of a wire manufacturing plant, Banker Wire, in Mukwonago, Wisconsin, that is in his congressional district.
Employee Keith Ketzler said Republicans promised that they had a plan but "all I see is in-fighting." 
Ketzler added Congress appears to be "very dysfunctional."
Ryan answered, "Believe me, I understand your frustration."
